<div id="review_3488710187" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3488710187" />
    <a title="Eirene" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23280329-eirene"><img alt="Eirene" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1491725215p2/23280329.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3488710187?book_show_action=true">Aug 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eirene" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eirene" href="/user/show/23280329-eirene">Eirene</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3488710187" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13899508653002196164">It is a very good story, which makes you want to keep reading. The writer has done a very good research of the recent history of Egypt and the historical background fits in well with the plot. However, reading about what life is like for women in a Muslim country made me angry, really angry. Useful though it may be for books with such descriptions to be written, I find them unsettling for my peace of mind. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


