<span id="freeTextContainer12709411323626914612">as much as I&apos;m loving this book, I have to point out many mistakes in quoting the quran! It is said that in the 38th verse of the 4th sura it is written that men are superior to woman! I looked it up, this verse doesn&apos;t talk about men or women at all so I don&apos;t know where they got that!<br/><br/>review after finishing: This book captured my attention like none other. I&apos;m Egyptain so I knew the traditions, it wad relatable. Somethings were a bit too over the top but it didn&apos;t bother me. All the characters </span>
  <span id="freeText12709411323626914612" style="display:none">as much as I'm loving this book, I have to point out many mistakes in quoting the quran! It is said that in the 38th verse of the 4th sura it is written that men are superior to woman! I looked it up, this verse doesn't talk about men or women at all so I don't know where they got that!<br /><br />review after finishing: This book captured my attention like none other. I'm Egyptain so I knew the traditions, it wad relatable. Somethings were a bit too over the top but it didn't bother me. All the characters were three dimensional and interesting to read. None were saints, none were too good or too bad. My favorite in the beginning, Nefissa, turned out to be a malicious woman which should have bothered me but it was so well written, that it just added to her character. The only thing that was not true to the traditions and culture was the easy way Khadija agreed on all the marriages between her muslim grandchildren and christian men. The many murders that happen in Egypt (not in Cairo but in Egypt) because of such marriages are so many! Even if Khadija would've agreed, the men and women in Al Tafla would not have tried to set Amira and Declan up. Yes Egyptains love weddings and love setting people up but it's against their traditions. Anyhow, awesome book</span>
  <a data-text-id="12709411323626914612" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
